questions.questionString: Out of 8 balls, one weighs less than the others. You have a scale. What is the minimum number of weighs to determine the ball that weighs less?
What does encapsulation mean in terms of object orientation?

option.optionString: The code is layered; typical layers are: user interface, business logic and persistence.
Logically related data and procedures are grouped in a class while hiding the internal behaviour and data structure for other objects.
Objects can only access their own attributes.
Encapsulation establishes the implementation, after that only the public interface can be adapted.

correctOption.optionString: Logically related data and procedures are grouped in a class while hiding the internal behaviour and data structure for other objects.

questions.questionString:
Consider the following code snippet: 
                        String s = "Chase the ball.";
                        StringBuffer sb = new StringBuffer(s);
Which code segment below produces a string equal to "Chase kicked the ball." using s and sb as shown above?

option.optionString:
sb.delete(6,15);
                                sb.append("kicked the ball.");
                                s = sb.toString();

sb.substring(0,6);
                                sb.append("kicked the ball.");
                                s = sb.toString();

correctOption.optionString:
sb.delete(6,15);
                                sb.append("kicked the ball.");
                                s = sb.toString();
